  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Antithesis> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Antithesis> ;
    narr:childCount "84"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "9e6de47a09c4033412445b86e926a65e6a4816d0" ;
    narr:narration """Antithesis serves as the foundational rhetorical and structural device across the aswritten corpus, functioning as a primary mechanism for [strategic reframing](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisReplaces), [decision taxonomy](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_FableWindowAntithesisPattern), and [product positioning](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_MVPRedef_Antithesis). The device manifests as binary oppositions—such as [procedural vs. human-driven](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AgentSim_Antithesis) or [conviction vs. temporality](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisConvictionTemporality)—that clarify principles by naming their inverse. While structural antithesis remains pervasive in [architectural](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisStructure) and [sales framing](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_AntithesisTriggers), a significant shift occurred in June 2026: the [prohibition of the 'X, not Y' sentence-closing pattern](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_NoXNotYAntithesis). This [prescriptive position](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_NoXNotY) mandates that load-bearing contrast be rebuilt through momentum structures rather than terminal negation. Despite this, the corpus continues to utilize antithesis for [skeptic-preservation](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_DavidNolen_SkepticalVoiceContrast) and [three-axis counter-positioning against AGI](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_SII_ThreeAxisAntithesis), maintaining a tension between the prohibited sentence-level device and the continued structural reliance on binary opposition.""" ;
